resources.description: Find all accounts in the helpdesk system.

parameters.name: where
parameters.description: The CEQL search expression, or the where clause, without the WHERE keyword, in a typical SQL query. For example, to search for objects where name equals foo, the search expression will be sys_updated_on='2016-02-08T07:09:41'. When this parameter is omitted, all objects are returned in a paginated fashion.

parameters.name: page
parameters.description: The page number. When this parameter is omitted, 1 is implied.

parameters.name: pageSize
parameters.description: The number of results to fetch in a given page. When this parameter is omitted, 200 results are returned.

parameters.name: accounts
parameters.description: The accounts object to be updated. The required fields indicated in the 'accounts' model are those required to update an accounts.
